helpdesk-ticket.subject: Jenzabar RDP certificate
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I noticed that the Jenzabar RDP server has a new certificate since the last time I used it. The certificate is self-signed and the signing certificate is not trusted. Can you confirm that this server does indeed have a self-signed certificate and whether there are any additional measures users should take to verify it? I’m connecting from the wired connection in my office.
Thank You,
Dr. Durant

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mary,
This is the request that Mike and I talked to you a bit about when we were asking about FERPA. Would you approve this type of access for Communication Officers?
We won't give them a generic account. Instead Mike and I would create individual Jenzabar accounts for each officer.
Do you have a current Jenzabar group that would work for this request? We can create a new one if you think that's necessary, otherwise, we were thinking an InfoMaker report could also work using NAME, *LHP, ADR2, and PHONE for any student that isn't FERPA restricted. I'm not sure if that is the best route though since it would be a huge report.
Let us know if you would approve this type of access along with what that access should look like. I can send you the name of the officers once I have them.
Jasmine
helpdesk-note.body-html:

This is the request that Mike and I talked to you a bit about when we were asking about FERPA. Would you approve this type of access for Communication Officers?

Do you have a current Jenzabar group that would work for this request? We can create a new one if you think that's necessary, otherwise, we were thinking an InfoMaker report could also work using NAME, *LHP, ADR2, and PHONE for any student that isn't FERPA restricted. Let us know if you would approve this type of access along with what that access should look like. I can send you the name of the officers once I have them.

Jasmine

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jasmine—
Most of the information is directory information so we can give it out unless the student has blocked the release of their directory information (name_master.is_ferpa_restricted). So, that covers name, addresses, phone numbers, whether they are enrolled or not. Birth date is not directory information. So they can confirm birthdate but can’t give it out without a subpoena or a written release from the student.
To be honest, a report on their workspace might be better. I can make a Jenzabar group but they would need to understand FERPA and I am not sure they will take the time to know it. Could you maybe do a report where they enter the last name or something as search criteria to pull people up so it doesn’t get crazy big? And maybe the report could list the name of FERPA restricted people but not their information? Like in place of address it could say FERPA restricted or something?
Mary
Mary Nielsen Registrar Milwaukee School of Engineering

To be honest, a report on their workspace might be better.  I can make a Jenzabar group but they would need to understand FERPA and I am not sure they will take the time to know it.  Could you maybe do a report where they enter the last name or something as search criteria to pull people up so it doesn’t get crazy big?   And maybe the report could list the name of FERPA restricted people but not their information?  Like in place of address it could say FERPA restricted or something?
 
Mary

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jordan Ketchum, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10517
Student in MLH trying to use Xbox Live gets "Couldn't find the Teredo IP address".
The Error in question is related to a failure to bond to a IP v6 interface. We do not currently deploy IP v6 on our network. However the xbox is capable of operating with fully functionally over IP v4 despite the error. If you are still having issues with the device behind your personal router, I would suggest adding the Xbox to the DMZ on your router.
I encourage to read our FAQ on Xbox live connectivity http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/support/solutions/articles/1000017081-xbox-one-cannot-get-a-teredo-ip-address
Thanks,
Cameron Wilson Information Technology
Assistant System Admin 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 14.10 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 14.10 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox
5.    Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7.    Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: windows 10 problem with Enterprise Architect
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Using my school Elite x2 tablet and the Software Center, I tried to install Enterprise Architect 11 this morning. It starts up fine, but as soon as I try to open the default project (“EAExample”), EA crashes (more specifically, I get the message “Enterprise Architect – UML Development Tool as stopped working”). The same thing happens if I try to create a new diagram and add a class to it or open an existing diagram. I’ve also tried uninstalling and mapping to \\neo.msoe.edu\App_Root<file://neo.msoe.edu/App_Root> and installing from there; it crashed again. This is relevant because a colleague, Chris Taylor, was able to run it fine after installing directly from \\neo.msoe.edu\App_Root<file://neo.msoe.edu/App_Root>. As I see it, there are two major differences between our computers:
· I have installed the Anniversary Edition update to Windows 10, he has not.
· He did not go through Software Center to install EA 11 but went directly to \\neo<file://neo>. I installed it from Software Center first and then tried reinstalling it in other ways when the first installation did not work. I have a workaround: running EA in a virtual box with Windows 7 installed on the virtual box. But this is not a clean solution. This may also be a problem that will affect Juniors who receive new laptops with Windows 10 installed on it.
Rob

·       I have installed the Anniversary Edition update to Windows 10, he has not.
·       He did not go through Software Center to install EA 11 but went directly to \\neo. I installed it from Software Center first and then tried reinstalling it in other ways when the first installation did not work.
I have a workaround: running EA in a virtual box with Windows 7 installed on the virtual box. But this is not a clean solution. This may also be a problem that will affect Juniors who receive new laptops with Windows 10 installed on it.
 
Rob

I received a notification from the IT department on May 27, 2016, concerning the senior gifting procedure because I attended the May graduation; I actually did not graduate until August 18, 2016. I spoke with an IT staff member back in May, and they said everything should be fine to use the computer through the summer. helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Billy,
I added page numbers and department info to the Parking Deduction Report for you.
Unfortunately, we won't be able to put the same executable on your computer that Willie has. It was originally created when we had Jenzabar and InfoMaker installed directly on our computers. So if someone (like Willie and I) had InfoMaker installed on their computer previously, they would still be able to run that old executable.
We will need to provide an alternate option since we are in the cloud. It is very simple though. We will just need to add the Jenzabar cloud link to your office computer. Do you have time for me to stop by today?
Jasmine

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Re: windows 10 problem with Enterprise Architect
helpdesk-ticket.description:
After additional experimentation, I believe it’s clear that the problem is that EA 11 is not compatible with the anniversary update. According to Sparx Systems, there is no claim that EA 11 works with Windows 10 and they recommend moving to version 12. The discussion I read is at http://sparxsystems.com/forums/smf/index.php/topic,31368.msg231140.html#msg231140
I have Windows 10 running under a virtual box on my home computer. I was able to install EA 11 on the virtual box and it seemed to run OK using the “old” version of Windows 10. But when I installed the anniversary update on the image, EA 11 stopped working (exhibiting the behavior discussed below).
Rob
From: Rob Hasker <hasker@msoe.edu> Date: Tuesday, August 30, 2016 at 1:00 PM To: Helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu> Subject: windows 10 problem with Enterprise Architect
Using my school Elite x2 tablet and the Software Center, I tried to install Enterprise Architect 11 this morning. It starts up fine, but as soon as I try to open the default project (“EAExample”), EA crashes (more specifically, I get the message “Enterprise Architect – UML Development Tool as stopped working”). The same thing happens if I try to create a new diagram and add a class to it or open an existing diagram. I’ve also tried uninstalling and mapping to \\neo.msoe.edu\App_Root<file://neo.msoe.edu/App_Root> and installing from there; it crashed again. This is relevant because a colleague, Chris Taylor, was able to run it fine after installing directly from \\neo.msoe.edu\App_Root<file://neo.msoe.edu/App_Root>. As I see it, there are two major differences between our computers:
· I have installed the Anniversary Edition update to Windows 10, he has not.
· He did not go through Software Center to install EA 11 but went directly to \\neo<file://neo>. I installed it from Software Center first and then tried reinstalling it in other ways when the first installation did not work. I have a workaround: running EA in a virtual box with Windows 7 installed on the virtual box. But this is not a clean solution. This may also be a problem that will affect Juniors who receive new laptops with Windows 10 installed on it.
Rob

helpdesk-ticket.subject: loading .xls files from myMSOE
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I have the school Elite X2 tablet running Windows 10 with the Anniversary Edition update. As standard, the tablet has Office Professional Plus 2016 installed. When I download the classlist from the Faculty Course Control section of myMSOE and open it in Excel, the file is apparently empty. Using a text editor I have confirmed it is an XML data file that does contain the list of students, and the same file does open correctly (with the full roster) using Excel in Office 2015. It appears the file format is incompatible with (at least my version of) Excel 2016.
A bit more detail: I generated the file by clicking on the Faculty tab, selecting the Class List option for a course, and then clicking on “Export to Excel”. I’ve confirmed that at least one colleague has seen similar behavior.
Thanks.
Rob Hasker

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 18.35 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

Current Usage: 18.35 MB

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.

8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.

If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Tablet Boot Problem Resolved - Somewhat
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Peter & Desk Techs:
I called and e-mailed today after I tried to use a USB 3.0 to VGA adapter and its drivers screwed up my tablet to the point it hung up during boot up. I resolved my own problem (by booting into safe mode and recovering from a restore point) but in the process found that it is extremely difficult to reliably boot the tablets into safe mode without first having Windows running (which kind of defeats the purpose of safe mode). I kept some notes on what I did, but now can’t reproduce the process.
I’m now trying to create a recovery drive on USB stick to see if it works consistently.
I’ll keep you informed and would appreciate any suggestions you have. However, the problem is no longer urgent.
Dr. Tritt

helpdesk-note.body:
Heather,
I don't know that this is going to be an easy issue to correct. We looked at it briefly in summer and again today, and the only difference we can find is that it works from all of the areas where MSOE replaced the network switches in 2012. However, the decision was made at that time not to replace the switches on the floors where the residents live. These switches are quite a bit older, and lack much of the complexity of the new ones. I can't say with 100% certainty it's these old switches, but I also can't find anything else that would cause the problem.
We have some ideas for a temporary fix: 1) change the IP address on our internal DNS for myfinancialaid.msoe.edu PRO: this will fix the problem for residence halls CON: this will impact ALL users, not just res halls
2) Ask the res halls to use wireless in the top or bottom floors where we've provided courtesy wireless.
We'll keep you posted because this same issue will affect one of our larger upcoming projects, so it will need to be permanently addressed.
Thanks,
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu

From: Dahlinghaus, Ian [mailto:dahlinghaus@msoe.edu] Sent: Wednesday, August 31, 2016 8:11 AM To: Google-Tony Subject: RE: MSOE Fall Class Schedule
Hi Tony,
You will need to contact the IT Helpdesk, helpdesk@msoe.edu<mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu>, with your problems.
For parking you may park in the Broadway Lot, which is directly across the street from the Student Life and Campus Center. A campus map can be found here<http://www.msoe.edu/about-msoe/visit-msoe/campus-map/>. Turn into the parking lot at Broadway and Highland Ave. You may ignore the “permit only” signs for your visit, but please email me with the make, model, color and license plate number of your vehicle if you have not yet done so. There is also a city parking lot across from the Grohmann Tower, but you will be required to pay. Street parking is also an option. Please let me know if you have any questions.
Agenda 5:30-6:00 - Networking 6:00-6:45 - Presentations on the following topics:
* Financial Aid * Tuition and Payments * Class Registration * Advising * Student Services * Campus Safety and Parking 6:45-7:00 - Brief Campus Tour
Thanks,
Ian Dahlinghaus Graduate Admissions Counselor Milwaukee School of Engineering Phone: (414) 277-7208 Email: dahlinghaus@msoe.edu<mailto:dahlinghaus@msoe.edu>
From: Google-Tony [mailto:tony1981tw@gmail.com] Sent: Tuesday, August 30, 2016 11:09 PM To: Dahlinghaus, Ian Subject: RE: MSOE Fall Class Schedule

Please advice!
Tony 1-414-803-3937
From: Dahlinghaus, Ian [mailto:dahlinghaus@msoe.edu] Sent: Tuesday, August 23, 2016 11:13 AM To: Tony Chen Subject: MSOE Fall Class Schedule
Hi Tony,
You have been registered for Fall Quarter – your schedule is attached. Now, there are just a few things that remain to complete your registration process.
I’ve attached the instructions for setting up your email/myMSOE account. It’s important to do this because professors will email you at your MSOE account and you will be able to register for courses in successive terms, view financial information, and access class information through myMSOE at www.my.msoe.edu<http://www.my.msoe.edu>.
You will need an ID card to access the buildings on the MSOE campus, including the Kern Center and the Library. The Campus ID Card production center is located on the mezzanine level of the Campus Center in the Student Accounts Office, room CC-437. They can be contacted at (414) 277-7460 or CampusIDCard@msoe.edu<mailto:CampusIDCard@msoe.edu>
You may also need a parking permit when you attend a class at the Milwaukee campus. The online application for a parking permit is here: http://www.msoe.edu/about-msoe/visit-msoe/student-parking-permit-application/.
Please note, while I have registered you for Fall Quarter, you will register yourself for successive terms. Instructions on how to use the registration system are also attached.
As for the paperwork that needs to be completed, there are some simple forms that you can complete online:
· Please fill out our privacy form located here: http://www.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-2047
· Please read and sign the Statement of Financial Responsibility located here: http://www.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-2345
· If you need more information about payment plans available to you, you can find more here: http://www.msoe.edu/community/admissions/financialaid/page/1430/payment-plans
Before classes begin, please go to https://msoe.blackboard.com and familiarize yourself with the website. It is likely your professors have not yet activated your classes in BlackBoard, but they should soon.
The paperwork can be scanned and emailed to me, dropped off in my office in the Rader School of Business (1235 N. Milwaukee Street), or mailed to:
MSOE Graduate and Professional Education 1025 N. Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202
Please let me know if you have any questions. I am happy to help!
Sincerely,
Ian Dahlinghaus Graduate Admissions Counselor Milwaukee School of Engineering Phone: (414) 277-7208 Email: dahlinghaus@msoe.edu<mailto:dahlinghaus@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-ticket.description: I changed my password about 10 days ago and I am getting email messages every day for changing it again. I am out of town until September 7 and do not want to change it again. First of all why should I and secondly I has been a major pain in the past when I tried to change it from out of town. Could you please take care of the problem and let me know if and what I need to do?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: I changed my password about 10 days ago and I am getting email messages every day for changing it again. I am out of town until September 7 and do not want to change it again. First of all why should I and secondly I has been a major pain in the past when I tried to change it from out of town. Could you please take care of the problem and let me know if and what I need to do?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Yvonne Yaz, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10624
Are you still experiencing problems with your password? Something to keep in mind is that changing your password off campus can result in some synchronization problems. I will try my best to explain the situation here as clearly as possible:
The password that you use to log in to your laptop, and the password you use to log in to your MSOE account are actually two separate passwords. When you are on campus, and you are connected to our network domain, the local password on your MSOE laptop is forced to sync with your MSOE account password. This allows you to type in your MSOE account password on your laptop and automatically log in to the MSOE domain in one single step. When you change your password from off campus, however, this forced sync does not happen. This means that until you come back to campus, your local laptop password will be different than your MSOE account password. So, if you changed your MSOE password online, your laptop password will not match, and if you changed your laptop password locally, your MSOE account password will not match.
SOLUTION: As soon as you get onto campus, all you should have to do is connect your laptop to the MSOE network (preferably by ethernet, as this works the best), and restart your computer to force the password sync. This will update both your local laptop password and your MSOE account password to match the most recent password change that you have made.
Please let us know if this explanation helps. If you continue to have issues, bring your laptop to the IT Helpdesk on the third floor of the CC building and we will be happy to help you out.
Thanks, Michael Logan helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Nathan Hansen, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10634
No. 5th year students are not eligible for laptop exchange. The reason for this is as follows:
The laptops that we hand out to freshman students are not owned by MSOE, but rather leased from HP. The laptop payments that students pay go towards paying the lease contract for that particular laptop. MSOE is expected to return each laptop leased from HP after each contract is up. To manage this in a systematic way, we divide the lease payments up into 6 installments, one installment per trimester, for 6 trimesters. After 6 trimesters (the time it takes for an on-track freshman to make it to the fall trimester of junior year), the lease is paid off. Since students entering their fall trimester of junior year have 6 on-track trimesters left, we exchange their laptops for the newest HP contract laptop. This laptop will be paid off in 6 terms without costing the student any extra.
Returning 5th year students do not have the luxury of 6 terms to pay off a laptop lease. So if we were to exchange your laptop, you would be stuck with the full bill (something like $2500), and would be expected to pay it all off before graduation. If you are willing to accept the bill, visit us at the Helpdesk and we may be able to discuss an arrangement. Otherwise, my personal advice would be to keep the laptop you have. The payments you have already made are enough to buy out your lease, so you will be able to keep the laptop as a "free gift from us" upon graduation, and you can buy a personal laptop for much less money that will suit any other needs you may have. I hope this helps!
Thanks, Michael Logan helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Sarah Broge, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10642
I apologize for the lack of communication. Let me start out by saying that the software we have at MSOE is not transferrable to your personal devices. This is because MSOE retains educational licenses for this software that is tied to our network domain. We cannot just hand out these licenses to students for contractual reasons. Therefore I would suggest you stick to using the laptop that we provide. I do understand, however that SolidWorks and AutoCAD may require large amounts of memory to run properly. If you have trouble running this software, you may want to buy an extra 4GB or 8GB RAM stick and have us install it for you. If you choose to go this route, please send us an email at helpdesk@msoe.edu so we can help you choose a RAM card that is compatible with your system. Please let us know if this information was useful.
Thanks, Michael Logan helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 19.43 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 19.43 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox
5.    Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7.    Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

I know everyone is very busy gearing up for the new school year and I wouldn't bring this issue up except that I use this email very frequently and need it to continue working properly.

Thank-you.

helpdesk-ticket.description: I'm a frequent user of my alumni.msoe.edu email account and noticed this week that the single-sign-on (SSO) portal web page between the Gmail login and the inbox seems to have an expired security certificate (8/30/15-8/30/16). This causes the SSO portal page to be considered a security risk by the browser. I have experienced this on multiple browsers on multiple computers with the same results. The email inbox can still be accessed if you proceed through the un-secure SSO portal page anyway. But then I changed my password thinking that might help (which it didn't) and now I can't get my phone to connect to my alumni.msoe.edu email. It has always worked flawlessly in the past until this week. I'm thinking it might have something to do with this expired security certificate on the SSO portal web page. Is there a way to renew the security certificate on the SSO portal web page? Has anyone else noticed this? I know everyone is very busy gearing up for the new school year and I wouldn't bring this issue up except that I use this email very frequently and need it to continue working properly. Please investigate and let me know. Thank-you. -Nate Brinkman '04, '11

helpdesk-ticket.description: While setting up my Xbox one in my dorm room in mlh i found out that i cant talk with my friends over a party. I've put mu Xbox one in the DMZ of my router, according to the FAQs on your website, and it is still giving me a "NAT Type: Unavailable" and when i test the multiplayer connection it says "Can't get a Teredo IP address" can you help?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: While setting up my Xbox one in my dorm room in mlh i found out that i cant talk with my friends over a party. I've put mu Xbox one in the DMZ of my router, according to the FAQs on your website, and it is still giving me a "NAT Type: Unavailable" and when i test the multiplayer connection it says "Can't get a Teredo IP address" can you help?

helpdesk-note.body: Sending to Paul the Xbox expert
helpdesk-note.body-html: Sending to Paul the Xbox expert

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Anson,
You may need to host the party or have someone else try hosting. The Teredo IP address error is also listed in the FAQ, but I'll attach the article here:
MSOE does not use NAT at this time. All IP addresses are internet-routable, and are not translated IP addresses. The IP you get when connecting to our network is the one that people outside our network see. You will only have a NAT if you are using a router or switch that provides DHCP other than the DHCP provided by MSOE.
That being said, we are familiar with what XBO considers NAT. The reason you may see errors along the line of "Can't get a Teredo IP address" is indicating that XBO did not get and cannot see an IPv6 network. MSOE blocks all IPv6 traffic as our servers, routers, and firewalls do not have policies in place to manage IPv6 traffic. All IPv6 traffic will revert to IPv4 if it cannot establish a connection. Use of IPv6 or IPv4 will not impact your network experience.
There are some steps you can take if you are using a router or switch between your device and our network. You can forward ports on your router to the IP address of your XBO. This will require giving the XBO a static IP address. You can also place your XBO in the DMZ of the route. This will also require a static IP, but is less effort than setting up port forwarding. This puts your XBO outside of the security provided by your router.
MSOE provides internet to students as best we can, while not sacrificing the safety or experience of other users. You may not get an Open NAT while on our network for the reasons above, as well as others. This should not impact the speed and quality of your gaming experience, but it may prevent you from hosting in some of your games.
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_address_translation http://support.xbox.com/en-US/xbox-one/networking/network-ports-used-xbox-live
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description: During my move here into the Grohmann tower I noticed that there was some functionality missing on my network capabilities. I often work from home and doing that requires me to be in contact with other users at Rockwell. I get an issue trying to connect to other users. I have also noticed this issue on my Xbox whenever I need to communicate to friends and family. I have noticed that there was a FAQ regarding a teredo ip address error. This was the same message that I was getting on my Xbox. Some of the methods I have tried to solve this issue is removing my router and connecting my Xbox/computer straight to the wall. Opening the appropriate ports listed on the FAQ. Turning on and off upnp. Turning on and off IPv6. Connecting through a wireless signal instead of wired. I have also noticed that there has been a massive amount of ping on the network lately that may contribute to my issue. After going through all these methods and getting no success I have reason to believe that the issue is out of my control and may be a firewall issue from msoe's network. I am hoping we can fix this issue soon as it appears I am not the only one having this issue and it is affecting multiple end users. Thanks.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Teredo
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
It has come to my attention that I have an issue with the schools network. I have moved in about a week ago and during that time I was required to work from home. Doing this I needed connect to Skype and contact other users for rockwell. I have had an issue connecting to any users with my headset and could not speak or hear anyone. I have noticed a similar issue on my Xbox in which I could not speak to family and friends. I ran a diagnosis and it had given me the error "could not find a teredo IP" . in this time I have looked and found an FAQ on the Msoe it website so it appears that I am not the only end user being affected by this. Some of the methods I have used to fix this issue are listed below
Reboot of router and device Factory Reset of router and device Plugging directly into the Ethernet port with no router between Opening up the correct ports listed on the FAQ turning on and off IPv6 Turning on and off upnp Using wireless instead of wired network
After all of these methods my issue still remains and I have not found a solution. This has led me to believe that the issue is not on my end but rather somewhere in msoe's firewall or configuration. Like I had stated before I hope this issue could be resolved as I am not the only end user with this issue. If you need to reach out to me I have listed my contact information below
Moataz Khalil 4142481335 Khalilmm@msoe.edu grohmann tower apt 902
Sent from my iPhone
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,

It has come to my attention that I have an issue with the schools network. I have moved in about a week ago and during that time I was required to work from home. Doing this I needed connect to Skype and contact other users for rockwell. I have had an issue connecting to any users with my headset and could not speak or hear anyone. I have noticed a similar issue on my Xbox in which I could not speak to family and friends. I ran a diagnosis and it had given me the error "could not find a teredo IP" . in this time I have looked and found an FAQ on the Msoe it website so it appears that I am not the only end user being affected by this. Some of the methods I have used to fix this issue are listed below

Reboot of router and device
Factory Reset of router and device
Plugging directly into the Ethernet port with no router between

Using wireless instead of wired network

After all of these methods my issue still remains and I have not found a solution. This has led me to believe that the issue is not on my end but rather somewhere in msoe's firewall or configuration. If you are attempting to use VPN in the residence halls, it will fail. The residents halls share the same class B network as the rest of campus, so VPN is not needed. VPN shouldn't be used on campus for the same reasons you've indicated. It was enabled on campus originally to allow staff to connect to our local ERP system, but that system is now in the cloud.
Where are you trying to use VPN?

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 20.94 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 20.94 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox
5.    Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7.    Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Widder,
From the error message, it appears you have a 64 bit version of MS Office installed on your computer which does not work with the 32 bit version of Visio.
Unfortunately, we currently support the 32 bit version of Office only.To make it work with Visio, you will need to remove your version of MS Office and install the 32 bit version from our Software Center.
Please let Helpdesk know if you need help with removal of the 64 bit version and reinstallation of the 32 bit version.

helpdesk-ticket.description: User unable to login to laptop after password change
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: User unable to login to laptop after password change

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi gorodetskyd, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10734
If you are having issues logging into your laptop after changing your password, you will need to connect to the campus network to re-synchronize your passwords. The best way to do this is by connecting an Ethernet cord to your laptop and restarting it. If this does not work, I would recommend attempting to change your password, waiting a few minutes, and then trying to restart the machine while plugged into our network. I will be marking this issue as resolved, however, should you require any additional assistance please feel free to contact us.
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi gorodetskyd,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10734

If you are having issues logging into your laptop after changing your password, you will need to connect to the campus network to re-synchronize your passwords. The best way to do this is by connecting an Ethernet cord to your laptop and restarting it. If this does not work, I would recommend attempting to change your password, waiting a few minutes, and then trying to restart the machine while plugged into our network. I will be marking this issue as resolved, however, should you require any additional assistance please feel free to contact us.

Thanks,
Thomas Schleich
helpdesk@msoe.edu
414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi prantil, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10744
We have corrected the licensing issues with Ansys 17 on all future installs, but people with Ansys currently installed with have to ether reinstall it or change the license server. To change to the license server launch the Client ANSLIC_ADMIN Utility (located in the Ansys 17 folder in the start menu) as administrator. Click Specify the license server machine. Select the current license server and click edit selected machine. Change the hostname to applicense2.msoe.edu and click save. That should fix the application. If you have problems you can also bring the computer into the CC helpdesk and they can do it for you. Mike can you please check if the ansys 17 server is running/working? Or have cameron do it if he is capable of it? Vince Prantil reported a couple teachers and 7 computers in the harley lab all had issues getting a license.
Thanks!
Thanks,
Cameron Wilson Information Technology
Assistant System Admin 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: software installation problem
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I get an error while attempting to install Engineering Equation Solver from the Software Center on my Elite x2 tablet. I get the following error: The software change returned error code 0x87D00607(-2016410105).
I have attempted several times and have tried restarting the computer. I am installing remotely but am connected via VPN.
Please advise on how to install the program.
Jeffrey LaMack, Ph.D. Program Director and Associate Professor, Biomedical Engineering Electrical Engineering and Computer Science Department Milwaukee School of Engineering
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I get an error while attempting to install Engineering Equation Solver from the Software Center on my Elite x2 tablet. I get the following error:  The software change returned error code 0x87D00607(-2016410105).
 
I have attempted several times and have tried restarting the computer. I am installing remotely but am connected via VPN.
 
Please advise on how to install the program.
 
 
Jeffrey LaMack, Ph.D.
Program Director and Associate Professor, Biomedical Engineering
Electrical Engineering and Computer Science Department
Milwaukee School of Engineering

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jeffrey LaMack,
Error 0x87D00607 occurs when Software Center cannot determine the location of the device. I was able to reproduce the error on a laptop connected from home over the VPN. If you wait a few minutes after connecting to the VPN it seems to correct itself. You may also want to try forcing a policy sync in Software Center by going to the "Options" tab, expanding "Computer maintenance" and clicking "Sync Policy".
Please let me know if this helps and you are able to install EES.
Thanks,
Chris Hougard MSOE IT Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10767

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 17.52 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 19.99 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 19.99 MB

Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox

6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.

8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-note.body:
This issue is NOT resolved.
I was able to direct my browser to box.msoe.edu and use SSO login to see my box.com files. However, this does not resolve the problem. I see my original problem description was ambiguous. I’m having a problem with the box sync app, Box Sync, not simply logging into box.com.
I have downloaded the and installed the box sync app. It asks for my SSO credentials when I run it. It is in response to entering these credentials that I get the Page Expired popup.
I have tried deleting my SSO credentials in Credential Manager, but continue to have the same problem.
I have tried uninstalling the box sync app obtained from box.com and installing the one obtained from msoe.app.box.com (they appear identical). I continue to have the same problem.
As indicated, the problem occurs when using a miniPC system I’m using from home. I also tried using my MSOE issued tablet. I cannot log into box sync from it either. I get the same error message. However, I have an older MSOE laptop that I used over the summer. I can and do use box sync on it. I can even quit and restart box sync on it without any errors.
Note – I keep my lectures and course materials on box.com. I cannot return the laptop until we get box sync working on my tablet. Any advice you can provide would be helpful. Given all the issues that arise during the first week of fall quarter, I do not consider this an extremely urgent problem, but I would like to get it resolved within a week or two if possible.
Dr. Tritt

helpdesk-note.body: I called the user and walked him through logging into the application. Something I have noticed in the past, it may default to SSO sign-in for the first box login, and I have seen this lead to the page expired error multipel times. If this pops up, selecting the "Use Box account credentials" so that it asks for both email and password on both logins resolves the issue. marking resolved
